course: main course
cuisine: Mexican
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Preheat your oven to 220°C. Halve, then remove the cores from the @red pepper{1} and @yellow pepper{1} and chop into 2cm pieces. Place the peppers on a lined #baking tray{} and drizzle over a splash of oil. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until slightly crispy at the edges, ~{15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, boil the @water{275%ml} in a large #saucepan{} and stir in the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Add the @buckwheat{150%g}. Bring back to the boil and cover with a lid. Cook on medium heat for ~{10%minutes}. Then remove from the heat and set aside (don't take off the lid!).

> The buckwheat is cooked when soft enough to eat - it won't be mushy though, it should retain a slight nuttiness!

Halve, peel and finely chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Halve the @green bullet chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed and finely chop. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Roughly chop the @chives{1/2}(roughly chopped) or snip them with a pair of #scissors{}. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{1%splash} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion and cook until softened, ~{5%minutes}. Add the chilli, @cumin{1/2%tsp}, @mild paprika{1/2%tsp} and @ground cinnamon{1/2%tsp}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> Some like it hot but if you don't, just add less chilli!

Add the black beans and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more, then remove from the heat.

Once the buckwheat is done (it should be dry not soggy), fluff it up with a #fork{} to separate the grains. Combine with your black bean mixture. Add the roasted peppers and stir through half the @crème fraîche{1}. Taste for seasoning and add more salt or black pepper if necessary.

Tip the buckwheat and black bean mixture into an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the cheese. Place on the top shelf of your oven. Bake until the top is beautifully golden and crisp, about ~{10%minutes}. Serve with a big dollop of crème fraîche and a scattering of chives. Enjoy!